        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Your family was large and poor, and you'd lost your place at the factory just as the war to end all wars broke out.  Too old for free schooling, too young to be an adult, you told every lie you had to to get into the Navy just as the Great War started.  It might have been easier to get pressganged, but you thought going through the proper channels would get you the chance to write your family.  You were rubbish at sailing, but you kept your head in battle and saved the life of an officer.  Your \"reward\" was a neatly arranged transfer to the Army, which redefined Hell for you.  You survived to the end of the War, but came away angry at everything, and unable to connect with your old life.   You ended up living on the streets of London for a time, until the Sabbat recruited you through a rescue mission front.  As you learned about the Sabbat's enemies, you understood why there was so much to be angry over, and you found the outlet you needed.  You were ductus of own pack by World War 2, and distinguished yourself in battle many times since then."
